The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, June 09, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Monday, June 9, 2003				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Chowringhee. Barricaded for flyover construction.				 																																	AJC Bose Road, in front of Calcutta Club and Rabindra Sadan. A flyover is coming up.				 																																	Southern Avenue. Construction on the drainage pumping station is in progress.				 																Talk				 																																	Amalendu De, president of The Asiatic Society, will deliver the Dr S.P. Sen Memorial Lecture 2003 on Indian Renaissance in Pre-Colonial and Colonial Context: An Analytical Study at Institute of Historical Studies Lecture Hall, on 35, Theatre Road, at 4 pm. 				 																Workshops				 																																	A workshop on Vedic maths at Padatik from 4 pm to 6 pm.				 																																	A workshop on stone carving for children, organised by Eastern Zonal Cultural Centre, at Aikatan, Salt Lake, from 10 am to 5 pm. 				 																Furniture				 																																	Furniture Show 2003 at Ice Skating Rink.				 																Photos				 																																	A photographic exhibition on the Medieval City of Gaur at State Archaeological Museum.				 																Pottery				 																																	An exhibition of pottery at Central Cottage Industries Emporium, Chowringhee, from 10 am to 7 pm.				 																Art watch				 																																	A retrospective of the works of Sunil Das at ITC Sonar Bangla Art-Gallery, from 11 am to 7 pm.
